Bug: read-then-write not atomic. Two requests `SELECT` same value, both `UPDATE`, one increment lost / same value returned.

Fix: do increment + read in one atomic SQL statement. DB handle locking.

```sql
UPDATE counters SET value = value + 1 WHERE id = $1 RETURNING value;
```

`RETURNING` give new value from same statement. No separate `SELECT`. Each concurrent request get own incremented value.

Node:

```js
